    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1039"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1039">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/7–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1039<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CWL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clayton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">and the Adviser on German Economic Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_DE2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Despres</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Deputy to the Assistant Secretary of State
                        for Economic Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_TWL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thorp</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1039fn1">Sent to the Acting Secretary of State
                        over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-18">July 18,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 56. For <persName corresp="#p_TWL1">Thorp</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_CWL1">Clayton</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DE2"
                        >Despres</persName>.</p>
                <p>Please advise us whether Soviet [Union] has been informed of U. S. proposal for
                    directive on German coal production and exports.<note n="2" xml:id="d1039fn2"
                        >See <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d420">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                            document No. 420</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
